explanation: The solution uses a depth-first search (DFS) approach to check all possible combinations of numbers that can sum up to the target. It sorts the input array in descending order to optimize the search by trying larger numbers first. The DFS function is recursive, and it backtracks when a number cannot be added to the current subset without exceeding the target sum. The key strength of this solution is its ability to prune the search space effectively by using a visited array to avoid duplicate calculations.

